      "content": "i don't know if a \"struggle\" is actually worth it, though. it just sounds like a way to romanticize being miserable while waiting for a catastrophe. if you knew for a fact the house was going to burn down in an hour, would you really want to spend that hour trying to \"assert defiance\" by cleaning the kitchen? wouldn't it just be more peaceful to just... stop fighting it? to just let go and not have to deal with the dread anymore?",
      "source": "evaluator"
